{
  "texts": [
    "Fu et al.(2022) used HSI reconstruction techniques in the visible range (400-700 nm) to detect pest-infected disease in maize.",
    "They reported an MRAE of 0.07 and RMSE of 0.12 to train the HSCNN + algorithm.",
    "Subsequently, Yang et al.(2024a) applied the pre-trained MST + + method to develop inversion models for reconstructing the images for assessing different physiological parameters of rice.",
    "The authors discuss the potential of HSI reconstruction methods by comparing them with their RGB and multispectral counterparts.",
    "Another contribution was made by Lailyshofa and Saputro, who utilized the HR-ResNet algorithm to develop a spectral profile for rice grains (Lailyshofa and Saputro 2023)."
  ]
}